<poem>
    <meta>
        <title>TO ——</title>
    </meta>
    <stanza>
        <l>I heed not that my earthly lot</l>
        <l>Hath <det value="closed">little</det> of Earth in it,</l>
        <l>That years of love have been <verb value="closed">forgot</verb></l>
        <l>In the <noun value="closed">hatred</noun> of a minute:</l>
    </stanza>
    <stanza>
        <l>I mourn not that the desolate</l>
        <l>Are <adj value="open">happier</adj>, sweet, than I,</l>
        <l>But that you <verb value="closed">sorrow</verb> for my fate</l>
        <l>Who am a <noun value="closed">passer-by</noun>.</l>
    </stanza>
</poem>